    {
      "id": "PopularPost45038",
      "post_content": "If this only costed ![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol), was a cip/etb-cantrip, or if it reduced the costs by ![3](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=3&type=symbol), this would be more interesting. Like this, it's mostly a pitious junk card.  \nNontheless my inner Johnny tried to find use for this card.  \n  \nSince it appears to be so bad, [Donating](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=15168) it seems to be an interesting idea. But don't forget that you'll also have to sacrifice a creature, and although it might even kill a control deck, it possibly won't have a notable effect on your opponent if he/she's playing a creature-based deck.  \n  \nOne of a few cases where this could find use over [Ashnod's Altar](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ashnod's Altar) is by byp\u00e1ssing the counter effect.  \nSo you could use cards which have this as inherent effect like [Obliterate](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Obliterate), [Urza's Rage](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Urza's Rage), which can act as [Lightning Bolt](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Bolt), or [Wreak Havoc](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Wreak Havoc) as ![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![Green](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=G&type=symbol) [Shatter](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shatter)/[Sinkhole](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sinkhole). [Banefire](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Banefire) will work... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Mode",
